Robot.

A Skule legend, but not everyone's cup of tea. Clear lectures, but which require you pay attention the whole time -- doze off and it's over. Provides brilliant note sets and the most detailed problem set solutions I've ever seen. Exams are based on problem sets, but still ridiculously difficult. Awesome bell curve.
One of the most overrated profs in UofT EngSci. The exam was ridiculous: 85% of the exam was on the hardest topics that she covered in last couple of lectures. Very bad class and very bad professor.

Too bad she's retiring.  Let me mention about the bell curve.  Given my two midterms and final, my average before the bellcurve was 50.3   I scored 75ish in the course after bonus tutorials and the curve..
nice prof! her mid-terms and exams are hard but her lectures are really well organized, i liked that course

Professor Yu-Ling Cheng sets hard tests and hard exams, and, as a lecturer, she isn't the clearest (though, to her credit, she's better than many).  Here course notes, however, are absolutely wonderful;  she has the dry sense of humour commented on before;  and she is willing to help.  A great prof.
If it's not because of Prof. Cheng, I would have die in this course.  She's the best prof in explaining such hard stuff. We all survived because of her. She's a great Prof.
Good professor, organised, challenging course.  Read course notes and do past tests.  She is always willing to answer questions, so there is no reason you can't do well.  Wonderful person.
